DO NOT DO THIS WHILE YOU ARE IN THE PROCESS OF BUYING A HOME!!!

Close financial accounts, quit your job, open new lines of credit, make large purchases, buy or lease a car! It can negatively impact you during your home-buying process.  You could potentially introduce a range of complexities as it can potentially disrupt various aspects regarding your financial profile. 

Your debt-to-income ratio, credit score, down payment, & cash reserves might all face adjustments. These changes can cause the lender to re-evaluate your loan application, leading to less favorable terms.  Last-minute changes can trigger delays and complications, jeopardizing a smooth transaction.

To ensure a stress-free & smooth transaction, it is crucial that you maintain financial stability. I STRONGLY advise consulting with your real estate agent and lender before you make any significant financial decisions during or at  ANY stage of your home-buying process.

Important Things to Check for when Buying a Home:

1. 🛖 How old is the roof? Roofs can be  costly and if there is less than 5 years of life left, you’d be wise to negotiate this into the price. 

2. 🥶🥵HVACs are another big ticket item. Look for a system that has been maintenanced YEARLY. Units can last 10-25 years. Talk to your inspector about the quality of life within ur existing unit

3. 🪠 Are there old trees with large roots at street? If yes, a sewer scope is in order. Check toilets, under sinks, piping in crawl space and hot water heater. 

4. MOLD 🦠 is a serious health hazard. Pay attention to musty smells and stains on floors and ceilings. 

5. 🎧Noise Level- Is the home on a major road? Near airport or railroad tracks? A townhome or condo? These can all impact resale value and your serenity!

6. Easy to spot foundation red flags include:
🚩 Cracks in foundation, exterior, drywall or ceiling
🚩 Gaps above doors and windows
🚩 Sunken stairs or porches 
🚩 Sloping or uneven floors or tilting 

7. It’s always best to hire an inspector to check out the ⚡️ electrical system in the home. They will also check the appliances!

8. 📍Buying in an area with a great location will increase your chances of appreciation. Your home is your biggest INVESTMENT!

It’s been predicted that the Fed will cut interest rates in 2024. What does this mean for home buyers and investors? 

Consider this - Nearly 90% of current homeowners are locked in at an interest rate of 6% or lower. Many homeowners want to sell, but they don’t want to trade their low rate for a higher one. So, they sit on the sidelines and wait for rates to drop. 

This has caused inventory to be extremely low while demand continues to increase in highly desirable and investor-friendly areas. 

If and when rates drop, there will be a buying frenzy, and home prices will likely increase.
